《'''威廉·麦克莱伦·“麦克”·索恩贝里2021财年国防授权法案'''》（H.R.6395）<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2020-12-15|title=H.R. 6395 (116th): National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2021 - Text|url=https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/116/hr6395/text|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210519180806/https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/116/hr6395/text|archive-date=2021-05-19|access-date=2021-02-03|website=[[GovTrack|GovTrack]]|dead-url=no}}</ref>是一部[[美国联邦法律|美国联邦法律]]，规定了2021[[财政年度|财政年度]][[美国国防部|美国国防部]]的预算、支出和政策。<ref>{{cite news |last1=Donnelly |first1=John M. |title=Congress girds for possible veto override votes on defense bill |url=https://www.rollcall.com/2020/12/17/congress-girds-for-possible-veto-override-votes-on-defense-bill/ |access-date=December 23, 2020 |work=[[Roll_Call|Roll Call]] |date=December 17, 2020 |archive-date=2021-01-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120233852/https://www.rollcall.com/2020/12/17/congress-girds-for-possible-veto-override-votes-on-defense-bill/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>该法案是为了纪念[[麥克·索恩貝里|麥克·索恩貝里]]<ref name=":2" />，他曾担任[[美国众议院|美国众议院]]军事委员会主席和高级成员。<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|date=2020-12-03|title=William M. “Mac” Thornberry National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2021|url=https://www.armed-services.senate.gov/download/fy21-ndaa-conference-agreement_-summary#:~:text=the%20William%20M.-,%E2%80%9CMac%E2%80%9D%20Thornberry%20National%20Defense%20Authorization%20Act%20for%20Fiscal%20Year%202021,nation%20with%20pride%20and%20valor.|access-date=2021-01-02|website=United States Senate Committee on Armed Services|archive-date=2021-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421200358/https://www.armed-services.senate.gov/download/fy21-ndaa-conference-agreement_-summary#:~:text=the%20William%20M.-,%E2%80%9CMac%E2%80%9D%20Thornberry%20National%20Defense%20Authorization%20Act%20for%20Fiscal%20Year%202021,nation%20with%20pride%20and%20valor.|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Benning|first=Tom|date=2019-09-30|title=Rep. Mac Thornberry becomes 6th Texas Republican in House to announce retirement ahead of 2020 election|url=https://www.dallasnews.com/news/politics/2019/09/30/rep-mac-thornberry-becomes-6th-texas-republican-in-house-to-announce-retirement-ahead-of-2020-election/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210303081940/https://www.dallasnews.com/news/politics/2019/09/30/rep-mac-thornberry-becomes-6th-texas-republican-in-house-to-announce-retirement-ahead-of-2020-election/|archive-date=2021-03-03|access-date=2021-01-03|website=Dallas News|language=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>

这项7400亿美元的法案包括为[[美軍|美軍]]士兵加薪、美軍装备现代化，以及在美军从[[德国|德国]]或[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]撤军前需要更多审查的条款。[[美国总统|美国总统]][[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]曾威胁要否决这项法案，因为该法案没有废除1996年的一项立法以保护[[互联网|互联网]]公司对第三方在其网站上发布的内容不承担责任。该法案还包括一项条款，限制总统使用[[紧急命令|紧急命令]]来转移军事建设资金扩建[[美墨边境墙|美墨边境墙]]。<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|last=Somin|first=Ilya|date=2021-01-01|title=Congress Overrides Trump Veto of Defense Bill that Includes Tight Constraints on Use of "Emergency" Powers to Divert Military Construction Funds to the Border Wall and Other Projects|url=https://reason.com/volokh/2021/01/01/congress-overrides-trump-veto-of-defense-bill-that-includes-tight-constraints-on-use-of-emergency-powers-to-divert-military-construction-funds-to-the-border-wall-and-other-projects/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210228120518/https://reason.com/volokh/2021/01/01/congress-overrides-trump-veto-of-defense-bill-that-includes-tight-constraints-on-use-of-emergency-powers-to-divert-military-construction-funds-to-the-border-wall-and-other-projects/|archive-date=2021-02-28|access-date=2021-02-07|website=Reason.com|language=en-US|quote=Section 2801 of the Act limits the president's ability to use "emergency" declarations to divert military construction funds to no more than $100 million per year for construction within the United States. This largely closes the loophole Trump tried to use to fund parts of his border wall project, using an emergency declaration he issued in 2019, thereby laying claim to some $3.6 billion.|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite news|last=Demirjian|first=Karoun|date=|title=Bipartisan defense bill includes several rebukes of Trump’s record as commander in chief|language=en-US|work=Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/bipartisan-defense-bill-includes-several-rebukes-of-trumps-record-as-commander-in-chief/2020/12/03/c39304f4-35c9-11eb-8d38-6aea1adb3839_story.html|access-date=2021-02-07|issn=0190-8286|quote=The bill contains several repudiations of Trump’s use of the military on the home front as well. It limits the amount of military construction funding that can be diverted to domestic projects via a national emergency order to an annual $100 million — a far cry from the $3.6 billion Trump attempted to divert to his border wall project in 2019. It sets a ceiling of $500 million for overseas projects.|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224212758/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/bipartisan-defense-bill-includes-several-rebukes-of-trumps-record-as-commander-in-chief/2020/12/03/c39304f4-35c9-11eb-8d38-6aea1adb3839_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>法案中的另一项条款将要求美国国防部重新命名以[[南方邦联|南方邦联]]人物命名的美军基地。该法案还包含多项反[[洗钱|洗钱]]条款，有效禁止匿名[[空壳公司|空壳公司]]。

该法案于2020年12月11日在参众两院以无否决权的多数票获得通过。12月23日，特朗普動用否决权否决了这项法案。参众两院分别在12月28日和2021年1月1日投票推翻否决权，这是特朗普总统任期内唯一一次否决权被推翻。<ref>{{cite news|last=Ewing|first=Philip|date=1 January 2021|title=Congress Overturns Trump Veto On Defense Bill After Political Detour|work=[[NPR|NPR]]|url=https://www.npr.org/2021/01/01/952450018/congress-overturns-trump-veto-on-defense-bill-after-political-detour|access-date=1 January 2021|archive-date=2021-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127110450/https://www.npr.org/2021/01/01/952450018/congress-overturns-trump-veto-on-defense-bill-after-political-detour|dead-url=no}}</ref>

